<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-09-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-09-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="415" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d415">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">894.48B/95: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Woods</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-09-15"><hi rend="italic">September 15,
                                    1923</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received September 20—2:32
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>58. In accordance with authorization in your 151, September 11,<note n="28" xml:id="d415fn28">Not printed.</note> I presented to Count
                            Yamamoto, Prime Minister and Acting Foreign Minister, a draft for
                            $1,000,000 in favor of Earthquake Relief Board. Prime Minister showed
                            deepest emotion and gratitude.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Woods</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>